HEADWORD: Seconder
<hw>Sec"ond*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who seconds{3}
or supports what another attempts, affirms, moves, or proposes; <as>as,
the <ex>seconder</ex> of an enterprise or of a motion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Secondhand</ent>⟦br⟧
